&lt;div class="post-text" itemprop="text"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In layout.HTML, you need to pass the context.  You do that with a &lt;code&gt;.&lt;/code&gt; dot.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;    {{ template "contents" . }}
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Alternatively, you can pass the value of whatever var you want:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;    {{ template "contents" .tes }}
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;

&lt;p&gt;...and within the contents template, the dot context will be just the value of &lt;code&gt;.tes&lt;/code&gt;.  That helps limit the scope of sub-templates, not having to dot-walk to get to a value.&lt;/p&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;

