&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;mysql_query("INSERT INTO users_data (id, username, gender, locale) 
     VALUES ('.$id', '.$username', '.$gender', '.$locale')");  
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;

&lt;p&gt;You are creating a single string (with embedded variables) so the dots '.' are not required.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If either of the id or gender are number-fields then this is likely to be what prevents the data from being inserted (with the dots). (If they are numbers they don't require surrounding apostrophes either.)&lt;/p&gt;
