&lt;div class="post-text" itemprop="text"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;if-else&lt;/code&gt; blocks have their own scope. In your case &lt;code&gt;dat&lt;/code&gt;is not visible outside of them.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;You can declare &lt;code&gt;var dat []byte&lt;/code&gt; before &lt;code&gt;if (bundled == "true")&lt;/code&gt; to fix it.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Docs: &lt;a href="https://golang.org/ref/spec#Declarations_and_scope" rel="nofollow noreferrer"&gt;https://golang.org/ref/spec#Declarations_and_scope&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;You may also want to read: &lt;a href="https://dave.cheney.net/2016/12/15/declaration-scopes-in-go" rel="nofollow noreferrer"&gt;Declaration scopes in Go&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
