&lt;div class="post-text" itemprop="text"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;See the relevant section from the spec: &lt;a href="http://golang.org/ref/spec#Declarations_and_scope" rel="noreferrer"&gt;Declarations and scope&lt;/a&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;The scope of a constant or variable identifier declared inside a function begins at the end of the ConstSpec or VarSpec (ShortVarDecl for short variable declarations) and &lt;strong&gt;ends at the end of the innermost containing block&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Define it in the scope in which you want to access it: before the &lt;code&gt;for&lt;/code&gt; (in the scope of the &lt;code&gt;main()&lt;/code&gt; function).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Also note that &lt;a href="https://golang.org/pkg/fmt/#Sprintf" rel="noreferrer"&gt;&lt;code&gt;fmt.Sprintf()&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/a&gt; requires an additional parameter besides the ones to be printed: a format string. Either provide a format string (e.g. include a &lt;code&gt;%s&lt;/code&gt; verb for the &lt;code&gt;randomString&lt;/code&gt; parameter) or alternatively you may use &lt;a href="https://golang.org/pkg/fmt/#Sprintln" rel="noreferrer"&gt;&lt;code&gt;fmt.Sprintln()&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;func main() {
    var randomString string
    for i := 0; i &amp;lt; 10000; i++ {
        randomString = fmt.Sprintf("a%sa
", "test")
    }
    fmt.Println("Made 10000 random strings like", randomString)
}
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Output:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;Made 10000 random strings like atesta
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Try it on the &lt;a href="http://play.golang.org/p/IKHK3Z_Uec" rel="noreferrer"&gt;Go Playground&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;

