    ...
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Here you're creating a local variable (scope restricted to the current method, only) called &lt;code&gt;$conn&lt;/code&gt;.  Because you're working with an instance of the class, you need to access your class members using &lt;code&gt;$this&lt;/code&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;$this-&amp;gt;conn = mysqli_connect(...);
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Take a look at &lt;a href="http://php.net/manual/en/language.oop5.basic.php" rel="nofollow"&gt;the docs&lt;/a&gt; for further info.&lt;/p&gt;
